history.text: I love this movie in a culty sort of way
First of all, have you ever seen this movie?
What was your favorite part of the movie?
Everything Janis ian does
I'm not sure who Janis Ian is, is that a character from the movie?  I've seen it but it was a long time ago.
I know the actors, not necessarily the characters.
Yeah, she's the girl Cady (Lohan) makes friends with who isn't a Plastic
I recall thinking both Tina Fey and Tim Meadows were a bit miscast, did you agree?
No, I think they fit their roles well.
Who did you think was the best cast character in the movie?
Rachel McAdams as Regina definitely did the best job.
I like Rachel McAdams.  I had a crush on Ms. Lohan at the time, as well, as I remember.
I feel like this was Lohan's last sober film, and at that she still flubs a couple lines.
Yeah, it's unfortunate what happened to her and her career.  As to the movie, did you think it was valuable to watch?  Said differently, do you think it could teach someone something?
I suppose it could try - as the book source did - to point out the poisonous nature of teen cliques and divisiveness.
It doesn't always hit this mark but it has fun trying.
I wasn't aware a.) that there was a book or b.) that you'd read it.  Is it similar to the film?  Or is the book much better?
I haven't read more than reviews of it, actually. it's a non-fiction book about girl cliques.
Basically Tina Fey came up with the idea while reading this book
I'm having trouble talking about a single movie this long.  Hmmm, is there any part of the movie you didn't enjoy?
Amy Poehler's character was sort of painful
I feel like she existed so her and Tina could hang out.
I don't even remember her.  I feel like she's always hanging out with Tina in movies though.  I'll give Ms. Poehler one thing, she's got range (even if she didn't use it in the movie).
I read the movie was listed as one of the top 50 greatest teen comedies, what number do you think it got?
Fair point. (she plays Regina's mom, who had the weird fake boobs)
I'm sure it hit the middle of the list.
To me, it's like an early 2000s Clueless
Really, I would have thought it would be a top 10 in that category.
I can see that.
It's good but not John Hughes good.
I'd put it higher than Clueless, though.
John Hughes being of Breakfast Club fame?
Maybe. But definitely below Breakfast Club
Yes, lol

uid1response.feedback: It was pretty chill.  I tried to ask a lot of question so the conversation didn't stagnate.
